HEADWORD: Chenille
<hw>Che*nille"</hw> <pr>(sh⟦esl⟧*n⟦emac⟧l")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F., prop., a caterpillar.]</ety> <def>Tufted cord, of silk or
worsted, for the trimming of ladies' dresses, for embroidery and
fringes, and for the weft of Chenille rugs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

